<subSubSection id="15DE5FE0FF8FEF4CFF42FBD7FDF5FA25" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FBD7FA3BFB18" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FBD7FEE7FBC4" bold="true" box="[199,338,1122,1148]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Comments:</emphasis>
This is the second record of the species after its original description. 
<bibRefCitation id="3955719AFF8FEF4CFBCCFBD7FABFFBC5" author="Gorochov, A. V." box="[1097,1290,1122,1149]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" pagination="480 - 503" refId="ref32654" refString="Gorochov, A. V. (2015) Systematics of the American katydids (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Communication 5. Proceedings of the Zoological Institute of the Russian Academy of Sciences, 319, 480 - 503. https: // doi. org / 10.31610 / trudyzin / 2015.319.4.480" type="journal article" year="2015">Gorochov (2015)</bibRefCitation>
recently presented a record of the species for Puerto Bertoni, 
<collectingRegion id="9F00C289FF8FEF4CFD3AFB33FCF2FB18" box="[703,839,1158,1184]" country="Paraguay" name="Alto Parana" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Alto Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="25D34CFBFF8FEF4CFCD7FB32FC0EFB19" box="[850,955,1159,1185]" name="Paraguay" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
, a place nearby the Iguaçu National Park.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FB1FFD9FFAB4" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FB1FFEEEFB7C" bold="true" box="[199,347,1194,1220]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Bioacoustics</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="C5FF10EEFF8FEF4CFEEEFB1FFE43FB7C" box="[363,502,1194,1220]" captionStart="FIGURE 21" captionStartId="44.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[211,1377,185,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-29@44.[203,1385,181,1919]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURE 21. Calling songs of Phaneropterini and Scaphurae (Phaneropterinae) from the ParNa Iguaçu. A–C: Viadana (Viadana) piracicabae; D–F: Topana cincticornis; G–I: Scaphura elegans. A, D and G: sonogram of one echeme sequence; B, E and H: sonogram of two syllables; C, F and I: respective spectrograms." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6550109" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6550109/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 21A–C</figureCitation>
): The stridulation is performed by males during the day and at the beginning of the night. The echemes are composed by seven to 35 syllables. Each syllable is emitted with a quickly increase and after that a long decrescendo of intensity.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FAA2FDDCFA88" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" box="[199,617,1302,1329]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FAA2FE1EFA88" box="[199,427,1302,1328]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Dominant frequency</emphasis>
: 21.8 ± 0.7 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FA8FFE6EFAEC" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" box="[199,475,1338,1365]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FA8FFEF5FAEC" box="[199,320,1338,1364]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Bandwidth</emphasis>
: 3 ± 0.1 kHz.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FAEAFDFBFAC1" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" box="[199,590,1374,1401]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FAEAFE9BFAC0" box="[199,302,1375,1400]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Duration</emphasis>
: Syllable: 0.01 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF8FEF4CFE73FAEBFDFCFAC1" box="[502,585,1374,1401]" degrees="0.002" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" precision="55" value="-0.002">0.002 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5D7B0C6BFF8FEF4CFF42FA36FDF5FA25" blockId="39.[151,1436,1049,1437]" box="[199,576,1410,1437]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis id="6FB0D079FF8FEF4CFF42FA36FEEAFA24" box="[199,351,1410,1436]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Mute interval</emphasis>
: Syllable: 2 ± 
<geoCoordinate id="38F06AACFF8FEF4CFD81FA37FD8EFA25" box="[516,571,1410,1437]" degrees="0.5" direction="south" orientation="latitude" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" precision="5555" value="-0.5">0.5 s</geoCoordinate>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
